  <Service>
    <name>Mercury Orbital Data Explorer</name>
    <abstract_desc>The Mercury Orbital Data Explorer (ODE) provides cross-mission and cross-instrument faceted product search, interactive map search, display, and download options for selections from planetary data archives.</abstract_desc>
    <url>https://ode.rsl.wustl.edu/mercury</url>
    <service_type>Service</service_type>
    <interface_type>GUI</interface_type>
    <category>Analysis</category>
    <category>Dissemination</category>
    <category>Search</category>
    <category>Visualization</category>
    <description>The Mercury Orbital Data Explorer (ODE) provides cross-mission and cross-instrument faceted product search, interactive map search, display, and download options for selections from planetary data archives. ODE includes a REST API for querying the ODE database from scripts, code, and other tools. Data from the following mission are cataloged in ODE: MESSENGER (Mercury Surface, Space Environment, Geochemistry, and Ranging). A granular data system (GDS) supports retrieving subsets of point data from MESSENGER MLA products, with output in the form of CSV files, GIS shape files, and binned images.</description>
  </Service>
